  "notes": "Icelandic (íslenska). Most conservative modern North Germanic language. PRESERVED: 4-case system; 3 grammatical genders; subjunctive; thorn þ [θ] and eth ð [ð]; full umlaut (y, ø, œ). UNIQUE: Voiceless sonorants — hl [l̥], hn [n̥], hr [r̥]. PREASPIRATION: ⟨pp tt kk⟩ = [ʰp ʰt ʰk] (retroflex in medial). ⟨u⟩ = [ʏ] (front rounded!); ⟨á⟩ = [au]; ⟨au⟩ = [øɪ]. No stød, no tonal accent. Source: Árnason (2011).",
